elSpec` are package-private, so I can't access them directly. But I'm wondering if I can set them through deserialization. That could be a workaround worth investigating!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Explaining coverage limitations**\\n\\nI need to clarify that no further changes can be supported because the artifact class lacks SourceFile and LineNumberTable. As a result, the coverage report is unable to mark call sites as covered, even though JaCoCo shows that read/write methods were executed. While the user asked for improvements, it looks like after my attempts, the best I can do here is to explain this limitation clearly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing object serialization tests**\\n\\nI’m considering how object serialization works with private methods in Java that depend on reflection for `writeObject` and `readObject`. Even though the dynamic calls are covered, I wonder if we can improve our test coverage using specific Jacoco options. However, it seems that adding new tests might not be necessary. I'm thinking we should leave the current test as it is. Transparency about our testing process is essential here.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "I investigated why the added `JCEElGamalPrivateKeyTest` still does not mark the two call sites as covered.\n\nThe test does execute the target methods on the JVM: the existing JaCoCo report shows both methods covered at method/instruction level:\n\n- `JCEElGamalPrivateKey.readObject(ObjectInputStream)` — covered\n- `JCEElGamalPrivateKey.writeObject(ObjectOutputStream)` — covered\n\nHowever, the dynamic-access coverage task marks call sites as covered only when the native-image dynamic-access frame has a source line and that line is covered by JaCoCo. For this artifact, `JCEElGamalPrivateKey` in `bcprov-jdk18on-1.77.jar` is stripped of source/line debug attributes. The native-image dynamic-access report therefore contains:\n\n- `org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.JCEElGamalPrivateKey.readObject(Unknown Source)`\n- `org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.JCEElGamalPrivateKey.writeObject(Unknown Source)`\n\nBecause the parsed line is `null`, the coverage task cannot mark these call sites as covered, even though the test reaches the methods.\n\nI did not make another code change in this iteration because the remaining gap is caused by the tested artifact lacking line-number metadata, not by an unexercised public behavior path. Covering it via a shadow/debug replacement class or modifying coverage infrastructure would violate the task constraints.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_00808c74df313d6a016a25ffa457188195bc45073564ed26d9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 850, "output": 1851, "cacheRead": 94208, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 96909, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780875133526, "responseId": "resp_00808c74df313d6a016a25ff7e310481958875a72dc11c2579"}, "toolResults": []}
